# Demo Honesty

ChatCRM is an **in-memory demo**. UI and copy must not mislead users into thinking production infra exists.

## What is real (in the browser)

- React UI, client-side state in `StoreProvider`
- Seeded data from `src/data/*.ts`
- RFM / CLV / cadence calculations (client-side, fixed demo date)

## What is simulated (say so in UI if adding related features)

| Feature | Reality |
|---------|---------|
| WhatsApp inbox | Mock messages in `store.messages` |
| Export CSV | Toast + audit log only — no file generation unless explicitly implemented |
| Login | Agent picker — no password auth |
| Billing settings | Placeholder UI |
| Persistence | **None** — refresh resets state |
| Backend / API | **None** — do not add `fetch`, tRPC, Supabase unless user requests full backend |

## Copy rules for demo features

- OK: `(demo)`, `File CSV berhasil diunduh (demo)` — matches existing export toasts
- OK: `Demo mode — pilih role untuk melihat perbedaan akses.`
- Not OK: "Data tersimpan ke cloud", "Pesan terkirim ke WhatsApp", "Sinkronisasi real-time"

## Do not add without explicit ask

- Fake loading spinners for instant in-memory ops
- OAuth / API keys / `.env` usage in app code
- "Production-ready" auth, rate limiting, or webhooks
- Marketing landing copy inside the authenticated app

## If user asks for "real" backend

Stop and clarify scope: database, auth provider, WhatsApp API — then plan separately from demo rules.
